Classes/SQLiteDB.html#/s:9PhotoTool8SQLi.name: DB_NAME
Classes/SQLiteDB.html#/s:9PhotoTool8SQLi.abstract: The SQLite database file name - defaults to data.db.

Classes/SQLiteDB.html#/s:9PhotoTool8SQLi.name: shared
Classes/SQLiteDB.html#/s:9PhotoTool8SQLi.abstract: Singleton instance for access to the SQLiteDB class

Classes/SQLiteDB.html#/s:9PhotoTool8SQLi.name: openDB(copyFile:)
Classes/SQLiteDB.html#/s:9PhotoTool8SQLi.abstract: Open the database specified by the DB_NAME variable and assigns the internal DB references. If a database is currently open, the method first closes the current database and gets a new DB references to the current database pointed to by DB_NAME

Classes/SQLiteDB.html#/s:9PhotoTool8SQLi.name: dbDate(date:)
Classes/SQLiteDB.html#/s:9PhotoTool8SQLi.abstract: Returns an ISO-8601 date string for a given date.

Classes/SQLiteDB.html#/s:9PhotoTool8SQLi.name: execute(sql:parameters:)
Classes/SQLiteDB.html#/s:9PhotoTool8SQLi.abstract: Execute SQL (non-query) command with (optional) parameters and return result code

Classes/SQLiteDB.html#/s:9PhotoTool8SQLi.name: query(sql:parameters:)
Classes/SQLiteDB.html#/s:9PhotoTool8SQLi.abstract: Run an SQL query with (parameters) parameters and returns an array of dictionaries where the keys are the column names

Classes/SQLiteDB.html#/s:9PhotoTool8SQLi.name: set(version:)
Classes/SQLiteDB.html#/s:9PhotoTool8SQLi.abstract: Set the current DB version, a user-defined version number for the database. This value can be useful in managing data migrations so that you can add new columns to your tables or massage your existing data to suit a new situation.

Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.name: init()
Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.abstract: Base initialization which sets up the table name and then verifies that the table exists in the DB, and if it does not, creates it.

Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.name: primaryKey()
Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.abstract: The primary key for the table - defaults to id. Override this in SQLTable sub-classes to define a different column name as the primary key.

Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.name: ignoredKeys()
Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.abstract: An array of property names (in a sub-classed instance of SQLTable) that are to be ignored when fetching/saving information to the DB. Override this method in sub-classes when you have properties that you don’t want persisted to the database.

Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.name: rows(filter:order:limit:)
Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.abstract: Return an array of values for an SQLTable sub-class (optionally) matching specified filter criteria, (optionally) in a given column order, and (optionally) limited to a specific number of rows.

Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.name: rowsFor(sql:)
Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.abstract: Return an array of values for an SQLTable sub-class based on a passed in SQL query.

Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.name: rowBy(id:)
Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.abstract: Return an instance of SQLTable sub-class for a given primary key value.

Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.name: row(number:filter:order:)
Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.abstract: Return an instance of SQLTable sub-class for a given 1-based row number matching specific (optional) filtering and sorting criteria. Especially useful for fetching just one row to populate a UITableView as needed instead of populating a full array of data that you might (or might not) need.

Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.name: count(filter:)
Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.abstract: Return the count of rows in the table, or the count of rows matching a specific filter criteria, if one was provided.

Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.name: countInDiffer(columeName:)
Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.abstract: Run an SQL query with (parameters) parameters and returns an array of dictionaries where the keys are the column names

Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.name: remove(filter:)
Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.abstract: Remove all the rows in the underlying table, or just the rows matching a provided criteria.

Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.name: zap()
Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.abstract: Remove all rows from the underlying table to create an empty table.

Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.name: save()
Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.abstract: Save the current values for this particular SQLTable sub-class instance to the database.

Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.name: delete()
Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.abstract: Delete the row for this particular SQLTable sub-class instance from the database.

Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.name: refresh()
Classes/SQLTable.html#/c:@M@PhotoTool@ob.abstract: Update the data for this particular SQLTable sub-class instance from the database so that all values are updated with the latest values from the database.
